review_content:
I’ve tried so many highlighters throughout the years, both subtle and blinding. This one is definitely subtle, is great if you just want a sheer/natural glow...it’s not all that pigmented and is not at all your glimmery, reflective, blinding highlight. You’ll be disappointed if you are expecting a “wow” highlight. But, I feel like this was meant to be a softer highlight anyway. Only thing I’ll point out is that if you don’t use setting spray over it, it’ll fade quicker than you’d think (it fades quicker than many I’ve used) I can recommend it for sure if you want a hint of glow. Other than that, you should look elsewhere for a highlight that pops.

product_name: Benefit Cosmetics Dandelion Box o’ Powder Blush
user_specs: ['Eye Color Brown', 'Hair color Brunette', 'Skin Tone Olive', 'Skin Type Combination']
review_content:
It took me a surprisingly long time to try Benefit’s Dandelion box o powder, and now I wonder how I ever lived without it. If you are someone who never uses blush, this is the blush for you! This is literally a hybrid between a powder and a blush, almost a non-blush blush, if that makes sense. The color is very buildable and is the most soft, natural looking color of pink I’ve ever seen. I have light olive skin and prefer a very natural makeup look, and in the summertime I can use this all over my face similar to a setting powder. I can use it all year round as a very natural looking blush that instantly perks up a dull or tired looking complexion. I do understand that for people with darker complexions and women of color, this blush might just not show up on them. It’s always worth testing in the department store if you can; even if you don’t like it as a blush you might consider it as a brightening setting powder.
